  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ojala! Spanish learning app for refugees</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ojala! is the first app to learn Spanish for people on the move. Offering courses in languages such as Wolof, which are not offered by existing apps and to people limited literacy, it can be an essential tool for migrants and refugees on the Canary Islands to access social and legal services and the labor market, as well as for integration into the local society. Beyond disseminating and improving the app, the team will train local teachers on the Canaries to teach Spanish as a foreign language.</narrative>
  </description>
